2.00	Nissl_substance	Nissl body	A Nissl body (or Nissl granule or tigroid body) is a large granular body found in neurons. These granules are rough endoplasmic reticulum (with free ribosomes) and are the site of protein synthesis. It was named after Franz Nissl, German neurologist (1860-1919).	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/81/NisslHippo2.jpg/200px-NisslHippo2.jpg
